						               													<description>User Description (English):&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We are in the last days of school prior to graduation of another class of students from the School of Dragons, a powerful institution teaching the doctrine of Draconaria, the art of training dragons.&amp;#10;It's time to find out who was the student who dedicated all his time to the secrets of the Dragon training, since only one student will receive the title of Master Trainer!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Escola de Drag&amp;otilde;es (School of Dragons) has only one goal: to find out which of the students is the Master Trainer. For this, the player must reach 25 points before his rivals, but beware, not always the other students will play under the rules (and probably you too)!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Escola de Drag&amp;otilde;es is a filler cardgame for 2-4 players (the use of 2 decks allows 5-8 players), no language needed and simple rules, where the interaction between players aims to undermine the possibility victory of the rivals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game uses a deck of 54 cards and is aimed primarily at children and young-adults (8+ years) or groups that don't have the habit of playing cardgames.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;User Description (Portuguese):&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Estamos nos &amp;uacute;ltimos dias de aula que antecedem a formatura de mais uma turma de alunos da Escola de Drag&amp;otilde;es, uma poderosa institui&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de ensino da doutrina da Draconaria, a arte de treinar drag&amp;otilde;es.&amp;#10;Chegou a hora de descobrir quem foi o aluno que se dedicou com maior afinco aos segredos do treinamento de Drag&amp;otilde;es, j&amp;aacute; que apenas um dos alunos receber&amp;aacute; o t&amp;iacute;tulo de Mestre Treinador!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Escola de Drag&amp;otilde;es s&amp;oacute; tem um objetivo: descobrir qual dos alunos &amp;eacute; o Mestre Treinador. Para isso, o jogador deve alcan&amp;ccedil;ar 25 Pontos de Treinamento antes dos rivais, mas cuidado, nem sempre os outros alunos jogar&amp;atilde;o limpo (e provavelmente nem voc&amp;ecirc;)!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Escola de Drag&amp;otilde;es &amp;eacute; um filler, ou seja, um jogo de cartas para 2 a 4 jogadores (usar 2 baralhos permite 5 a 8 jogadores), independente de idioma e com regras simples, cuja intera&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o entre jogadores visa minar a possibilidade de vit&amp;oacute;ria dos rivais.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;O jogo utiliza um baralho de 54 cartas e &amp;eacute; direcionado principalmente ao p&amp;uacute;blico infanto-juvenil (a partir de 8 anos) ou grupos que n&amp;atilde;o tenham o h&amp;aacute;bito de jogar cardgames.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
